Sun Crusher/Vehement/Shockwave:




Shockwave looked at the several tubes, finding it hard to believe his 
comrades' minds were inside them.
"So they are all alive?" he asked.

"Let me check, Emperor." Sun Crusher said, the last work with a mock tone.  
Putting his hand over a green-glass looking square he turned around to 
Shockwave.

"The unit Bumblebee did not make it an--"

"What about Unitron and Firestarter?" Shockwave interrupted.

"They are intact one-hundred percent.  Only five percent of Bumblebee made it 
in time.  Injector won't remember a month's time.  The others are fine as 
well.  It's only a matter of rebuilding their bodies.  Bumblebee's 
conscioussnes belongs to the Brotherhood though."

"Very well." Shockwave replied.  He didn't even know who Bumblebee or 
Injector were.  "You have the necessary parts?"

"They're on their way." Vehement replied.
